The paper discusses a system for analyzing XML data, which is typically stored in databases. Therefore, cs.DB is the most likely sub-category. The system also involves keyword-style querying and interactive refinement, which are common techniques in information retrieval (cs.IR) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of off-the-shelf OLAP tools, which are commonly used in data analytics and machine learning (cs.DL). Finally, the paper discusses the challenges of designing complex data transformations, which is a common issue in software engineering (cs.SE).
